com.dlsc.flexgantt.model.scheduling

Interface IConstraint<T,S extends IGranularity>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the object type of the timeline objects
    S - the granularity type (e.g. TimeGranularity.HOURS)
    All Superinterfaces:
    IRelationship<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConstraint, SimpleGranularityConstraint, TimeGranularityConstraint

    public interface IConstraint<T,S extends IGranularity>
extends IRelationship<T>
    A constraint is a specialization of a generic relationship between two timeline objects. It adds scheduling-specific information to the relationship such as constraint type (hard, soft) and buffer duration.
    Since:
    2.1
    Author:
    Dirk Lemmermann

    • Method Detail

      • getViolation

        Violation getViolation(long time1,
                       long time2)
        Checks whether a violation of the constraint exists for the given two time points.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.END_TO_START then time1will be the end time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the start time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.END_TO_END then time1will be the end time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the end time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.START_TO_START then time1will be the start time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the start time of the second timeline object.
        • If the constraint is of type RelationshipType.START_TO_END then time1will be the start time of the first timeline object and time2 will be the end time of the second timeline object.
        Parameters:
        time1 -
        time2 -
        Returns:
        a violation message
        Since:
        2.1
